HEADWORD: Calcigenous
<hw>Cal*cig"e*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>calx</ets>, <ets>calcis</ets>, lime + <ets>-genouse</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Tending to form, or to become, a calx or
earthlike substance on being oxidized or burnt; as magnesium, calcium.
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

